item.description:
TL;DR is Buff is an unconvential Windows box. Not your usual Kerberos, LDAP, SMB, etc. Chisel is much better than plink. Think smarter not harder. Read exploit details carefully
Enumeration  Nmap Starting with an nmap scan&hellip;
~ » nmap -vv --reason -Pn -A --osscan-guess --version-all -p- 10.10.10.198 Nmap scan report for 10.10.10.198 Host is up, received user-set (0.13s latency). Scanned at 2020-10-12 22:10:53 UTC for 599s Not shown: 65533 filtered ports Reason: 65533 no-responses PORT STATE SERVICE REASON VERSION 7680/tcp open pando-pub?

TL;DR: this is an easy UNIX box that could possibly be the easiest box on Hack The Box. Do basic enumeration. Type &lt;service&gt; &lt;version&gt; exploit into Google. Profit. Try not to use metasploit&hellip;
Enumeration  Nmap Starting with an nmap scan&hellip;
~ » nmap -vv --reason -Pn -A --osscan-guess --version-all -p- 10.10.10.3 Nmap scan report for 10.10.10.3 Host is up, received user-set (0.064s latency). Scanned at 2020-09-29 22:39:43 UTC for 177s Not shown: 65530 filtered ports Reason: 65530 no-responses PORT STATE SERVICE REASON VERSION 21/tcp open ftp syn-ack ttl 62 vsftpd 2.
